length()
Returns the number of characters in the string.
Example: "Hello".length() → 5

charAt(int index)
Returns the character at the specified position (index starts at 0).
Example: "Hello".charAt(1) → 'e'

toLowerCase()
Converts all characters in the string to lowercase.
Example: "Hello".toLowerCase() → "hello"

toUpperCase()
Converts all characters to uppercase.
Example: "Hello".toUpperCase() → "HELLO"

trim()
Removes leading and trailing whitespace (spaces, tabs).
Example: " Hello ".trim() → "Hello"

substring(int beginIndex)
Returns part of the string from beginIndex to the end.
Example: "Hello".substring(2) → "llo"

substring(int beginIndex, int endIndex)
Returns part of the string from beginIndex up to (but not including) endIndex.
Example: "Hello".substring(1,4) → "ell"

contains(CharSequence s)
Checks if the string contains the specified sequence of characters. Returns true/false.
Example: "Hello".contains("ell") → true

equals(Object anObject)
Compares two strings for exact equality (case-sensitive).
Example: "Hello".equals("hello") → false

equalsIgnoreCase(String anotherString)
Compares two strings for equality, ignoring case differences.
Example: "Hello".equalsIgnoreCase("hello") → true

indexOf(int ch)
Returns the index of the first occurrence of a character, or -1 if not found.
Example: "Hello".indexOf('l') → 2

lastIndexOf(int ch)
Returns the index of the last occurrence of a character.
Example: "Hello".lastIndexOf('l') → 3

replace(char oldChar, char newChar)
Replaces all occurrences of oldChar with newChar.
Example: "Hello".replace('l', 'x') → "Hexxo"

split(String regex)
Splits the string into an array based on the given delimiter (regular expression).
Example: "a,b,c".split(",") → ["a", "b", "c"]

startsWith(String prefix)
Checks if the string starts with the specified prefix. Returns true/false.
Example: "Hello".startsWith("He") → true

endsWith(String suffix)
Checks if the string ends with the specified suffix.
Example: "Hello".endsWith("lo") → true

concat(String str)
Concatenates (joins) another string at the end.
Example: "Hello".concat(" World") → "Hello World"

isEmpty()
Returns true if the string length is zero.
Example: "".isEmpty() → true

compareTo(String anotherString)
Compares two strings lexicographically (dictionary order). Returns:

0 if equal

Negative if this string is before the argument

Positive if after
Example: "abc".compareTo("abd") → negative number

toCharArray()
Converts the string into a char array.
Example: "Hi".toCharArray() → ['H', 'i']

valueOf()
Converts other data types (int, double, etc.) to string.
Example: String.valueOf(10) → "10"
